Identifiers :-
#. It is a name of the basic programming elements.
Rules :-
1. Identifier should only contain below fashion :-
#. Alphabets - [a to z] and [A to Z]
#. Digits: [0 to 9]
#. Special Charaters - [or $]
2. Identifiers should not start with a digit. A digit can be used from 2nd chararcter onwards.
3. Identifier should not contain space in the middle of the words. If we want to provide gap between words, they must be connected with '_'
4. Identifier is case sensitive (a != A)
